### Test 1: Create a new game and add to user library
POST http://localhost:3000/api/user-games
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "1",
  "gameId": "1",
  "relationship": "OWNED",
  "source": "Kickstarter",
  "game": {
    "name": "Catan",
    "imageUrl": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1570303228200-61b3c5f6e4d9",
    "minPlayers": 4,
    "maxPlayers": 4,
    "playTime": 90
  }
}

### Test 2: Add same game to another user's library
POST http://localhost:3000/api/user-games
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "2",
  "gameId": "1",
  "relationship": "PLAYED_ELSEWHERE"
}

### Test 3: Add a different game for the same user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/user-games
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "test-user-1",
  "gameId": "ticket-to-ride-001",
  "relationship": "WISHLIST",
  "game": {
    "name": "Ticket to Ride",
    "imageUrl": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1516975080664-ed2fc6a32937",
    "minPlayers": 2,
    "maxPlayers": 5,
    "playTime": 60
  }
}

### Test 4: Try to add duplicate (should fail with 409)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/user-games
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "test-user-1",
  "gameId": "catan-001",
  "relationship": "OWNED"
}

### Test 5: Missing required field (should fail with 400)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/user-games
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "1",
  "gameId": "missing-relationship"
}

### Test 6: Invalid relationship (should fail with 400)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/user-games
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "1",
  "gameId": "invalid-game",
  "relationship": "INVALID_TYPE"
}

### Test 7: Get all games in user's library
GET http://localhost:3000/api/user-games?userId=1
Accept: application/json